chunks.title: Custom Instant Shelters & Gazebos
chunks.chunk:
## Overview
- Turn required outdoor shelters into branded marketing space with custom canopies and walls.
- Supply your own structure or choose from curated gazebos tested for commercial use.
- Replacement canopies/walls available to refresh existing frames.

chunks.title: Custom Instant Shelters & Gazebos
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering Workflow
1. **Select Your Canvas** – drop off an existing gazebo or pick from vetted models.
2. **Free Quote & Mockup** – send logos for visual concepts; in-house designers can build artwork or logos if needed.
3. **Approval** – upon sign-off, production typically takes 5–10 working days (rush timelines on request).
4. **Fulfilment** – collect from Kidderminster or request delivery.

chunks.title: Custom Instant Shelters & Gazebos
chunks.chunk:
## Gazebo Options

### Mid-Range (Light Commercial / Markets)
- **Sizes & Pricing:** 3×3 m £175 + VAT, 3×4.5 m £200 + VAT, 3×6 m £265 + VAT (frame + canopy).
- **Canopy:** 100% waterproof 420D polyester PVC-backed fabric; colours include Black, Pink, Tan, Blue, Red, Grey, Brown, White, Purple.
- **Frame:** powder-coated steel with 32 × 32 mm box-section legs, 1.2 mm gauge framework, nylon joints, three height settings (1400–2100 mm).

- **Canopy:** 100% waterproof 600D polyester PVC-backed fabric; colour options include White, Black, Navy, Green, Red, multi-tone combinations, Purple, Pink, Grey, Orange, Yellow.
- **Frame:** reinforced construction designed for regular exposure to the elements; spare parts on request.

chunks.title: Custom Instant Shelters & Gazebos
chunks.chunk:

- Printed vinyl for multicolour artwork, gradients, photos, fluorescent or metallic finishes.
- Cut vinyl for sharp logos and lettering with no background.
- Panels (canopy peaks, valances, walls) can be wrapped individually; discounts available for multi-panel packages.

chunks.title: Custom Instant Shelters & Gazebos
chunks.chunk:
## Support
- Get help selecting the right gazebo spec, planning artwork coverage, arranging rush jobs, or sourcing replacement parts/canopies.

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Overview
- Glass manifestation is legally required on large transparent surfaces to prevent collisions and ensure compliance with Building Regulations (Approved Document K5.2) and DDA guidance.
- Etched or frosted window film makes glass visible without sacrificing style; decals can incorporate logos, patterns, or directional text.
- Suitable for offices, retail fronts, doors, partitions, bathrooms, and kitchens (condensation resistant).

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Why It Is Required
- Regulation K5.2: transparent glazing people may contact must include permanent markers to make it apparent.
- Markers must appear at two heights: 850–1000 mm and 1400–1600 mm from the floor, visible inside and out in varied lighting.
- Frosted films provide the necessary contrast and permanence while allowing natural light transmission.

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering & Installation Workflow
1. **Free Site Survey** – schedule measurement and photography, or supply your own dimensions/photos for remote quoting.
2. **Design + Quote** – studio prepares visuals showing pattern placement and any branding; logo creation support is available.
3. **Approval** – confirm artwork and pricing, then book a production/install slot.
4. **Installation** – fully insured fitters apply the film on site; DIY supply (roll or cut-to-size) also available.

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Customisation Options
- **Patterns:** choose from 16 stock designs or request bespoke motifs for subtle markers.
- **Text:** integrate wayfinding or notices that double as visibility strips.
- **Logos:** embed branding into the etched film for consistent identity.
- **Opacity Choices:** standard film allows ~80% of light; lighter or heavier frosts available plus coloured films.

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Installation Team
- Experienced technicians cover the Midlands, providing bubble-free application, access equipment, and optional removal of existing graphics.
- DIY customers can receive pre-cut panels and fitting guidance.

chunks.title: Glass Manifestation & Safety Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Care & Maintenance
- Wait at least 3 weeks before first clean.
- Use mild soapy water with a soft cloth; avoid abrasive pads or squeegees, especially on cut-out edges.
- For printed or layered films, wipe gently around exposed edges to preserve detail.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Overview
- Ideal for drivers who alternate between business and personal use or consult for multiple brands.
- Magnetic panels blend with vehicle paintwork using colour consultation and custom shaping.
- Media is 0.85 mm thick, speed-tested to 70 mph, and adheres to any ferromagnetic surface.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering Workflow
1. **Free Quote** – choose standard sizes (600 × 1000 mm or 600 × 500 mm) or request custom dimensions shaped to graphics/panels. Book a Kidderminster consultation for non-standard vehicles.
2. **Design Stage** – send artwork for proofing or supply logos for bespoke layouts; in-house logo creation available.
3. **Approval** – production lead time typically 5–10 working days; rush timelines handled case-by-case.
4. **Fulfilment** – collect locally or request delivery (from £10).

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Product Options

### 610 × 500 mm Panels (from £60 + VAT each)
- Suited to cars, small vans, pickups.
- Finish options:
  - Full printed graphic (matt or gloss lamination).
  - Colour-matched background (including metallic) with cut decals in matt or gloss.
  - Contrasting vinyl wrap background with cut decals.
- Colour matching done on-site or via Pantone/RAL references.

### 610 × 1000 mm Panels (from £75 + VAT each)
- Designed for larger vans; same finish options as above.

### Custom Size/Shape (from £150 + VAT each)
- Perfect for inset body panels; maximum single piece 610 mm (h) × 2000 mm (w).
- Vehicle library drawings used for standard models; consultations recommended for unique specs.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Colour Matching & Materials
- High-performance vinyl graphics rated for minimum 5-year exterior life under normal exposure.
- Colour consultation ensures backgrounds match automotive paint (including metallic finishes) so magnets blend seamlessly.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Care & Usage Guidelines
- Remove magnets at least weekly to clean/dry the bodywork underneath; more frequently in extreme weather.
- Wait for new paint (90 days), clear coat (60 days), or wax (2 days) to cure before applying magnets.
- Avoid non-flat surfaces with heavy dips/bumps; slight curves are acceptable.
- Expected lifespan ~2 years with proper care; inspect regularly to prevent drop-offs at speed.
- Remove before vehicle washing; store flat when not in use.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Customisation Methods
- **Printed Vinyl:** supports multicolour graphics, gradients, photos, metallic, fluorescent, glitter, holographic effects; laminated in matt or gloss.
- **Cut Vinyl:** best for simple logos/text with crisp edges; no background so base colour shows through; available in metallic, neon, and specialty finishes. Multiple colours are layered as needed.
- Team can recommend the optimal method based on artwork complexity, colour requirements, and budget.

chunks.title: Magnetic Vehicle Signs
chunks.chunk:
## Support
- Contact for size recommendations, colour references, rush orders, or advice on when magnets are preferable versus permanent signwriting.

chunks.title: Pavement & Forecourt Signs

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering Workflow
1. **Free Quote** – choose a standard panel size or request a complimentary site visit for measurements and photos (or supply your own).
2. **Design Stage** – send existing artwork for proofing, or provide logos/briefs for the studio to develop visuals; in-house logo creation available.

4. **Fulfilment** – collect finished boards from Kidderminster or arrange delivery (from £10).

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
## Material Options

### Aluminium Composite (Durable Exterior Board)
- Construction: twin coated aluminium skins with solid polyethylene core.
- Size: up to 8 × 4 ft (2440 × 1220 mm); larger signs use multiple panels side by side.
- Thickness: 3 mm with 0.15 mm aluminium skin.
- Finish: supplied white matt for vinyl wrap or decals; printable surface accepts gloss, matt, anti-graffiti, or dry-wipe laminates.
- Fixings: drillable for screw installation; colour-matched screwcaps supplied with installation jobs (available separately for supply only). Panels can arrive pre-drilled.

### Perspex Acrylic (Luxury Interior or Exterior)
- Use cases: premium building signage or wall art where a high-end finish is required.
- Sizes: custom clear or 35 opaque colours; thickness options 3, 5, 8, or 10 mm; square or rounded corners.
- Stock formats (5 mm clear): round 100/150/300 mm, square 100 × 100 mm, rectangles up to 420 × 297 mm, ovals from 150 × 75 mm to 300 × 200 mm.
- Finishes: gloss opaques (Clear, Opal, White, Black, Dark Grey, Grey, Violet, Sky, Azure, Brilliant Blue, Navy, Lime, Green, Kelly Green, Brown, Burgundy, Hot Pink, Red, Tomato, Orange, Golden Yellow, Yellow, Ivory, Cream, Gold, Silver, Mirror Silver, Mirror Gold); pastel matt or mid-gloss (Grape, Salmon, Peach, Lemon, Mint, Baby Blue, Powder Blue, Lavender). Mirror acrylic not warranted outdoors; only Clear and Opal are translucent.
- Fixings: typically installed with metal stand-offs (19×19, 13×19, or 25×25 mm) in chrome or satin; panels can be pre-drilled with recommended stand-off counts.

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
### Aluminium Sign Tray (Robust Exterior Sign)
- Material: 3 mm aluminium composite folded into a pan tray; multiple colours and finishes.
- Maximum single-piece sizes (includes returns): standard colours 3000 × 1460 mm, special finishes 2400 × 1200 mm. Larger trays supplied as multiple panels with tongue-and-groove joining strips.
- Colours: matt or gloss White, Black, Anthracite, Grey, Cream, Yellow, Orange, Red, Burgundy, Brown, Green, Dark Green, Azure, Deep Blue, Mirror Silver/Gold, Brushed Silver/Gold/Copper/Black.
- Fixings: delivered with required hardware for wall mounting.

### Foamex (Lightweight Interior Board)
- Applications: exhibitions, indoor signage, short-term exterior messaging.
- Sizes: up to 8 × 4 ft; common paper sizes available.
- Thickness: 3, 5, 10, or 19 mm.
- Finish: white surface ready for vinyl wrap or printed graphics; compatible with gloss, matt, anti-graffiti, or dry-wipe laminates.
- Fixings: mount using double-sided tape, Velcro, cable ties, or screws for added durability.

### Correx (Lightweight Temporary Exterior Board)
- Material: waterproof corrugated plastic ideal for temporary outdoor signage.
- Maximum size: 1230 × 1000 mm; stock sizes include 24×18 in (610 × 457 mm) up to 48×39 in (1230 × 1000 mm).
- Colours: White, Black, Yellow, Red, Green, Blue (vinyl wrapping/custom decals available).
- Fixings: hang with cable ties externally or tape/Velcro indoors thanks to low weight.

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
## Customisation & Finishing
- Printed vinyl graphics handle complex art, gradients, photographs, metallics, fluorescent, glitter, or holographic effects.
- Cut vinyl delivers crisp lettering/logos without a background and excels for solid colours.
- Lamination upgrades improve durability (e.g., anti-graffiti or dry-wipe for menu boards).
- Design support covers everything from layout tweaks to full creative direction or logo development.

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
## Installation & Support
- Panels built to specification using premium materials and high manufacturing standards.
- Professional installation (including drilling, screwcaps, access equipment) available across the Midlands; self-install kits include pre-drilled holes and fixings on request.
- Contact the team for guidance on selecting materials, finishes, customisation techniques, installation approach, or accelerated timelines.

chunks.title: Custom Sign Boards
chunks.chunk:
## Care Tips
- Wipe surfaces with mild soapy water and non-abrasive cloths.
- Inspect exterior hardware periodically, especially multi-panel joins or high-wind sites.

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths
chunks.chunk:

1. **Free Quote** – share table dimensions (length, width, height) plus preferred style (loose, fitted, stretch).
2. **Design Stage** – send artwork for proofing or brief the studio for bespoke layouts/logos.
3. **Approval** – once visuals and pricing are signed off, production typically takes 5–10 working days.
4. **Fulfilment** – collect locally or request delivery; storage and care instructions supplied with each cover.

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths
chunks.chunk:
## Fabric & Style Options
- **Polyester Throw (Most Versatile):** drapes over the table with box pleats or rounded corners; can cover 3 or 4 sides depending on access needs.
- **Fitted Cover:** sewn corners for a crisp silhouette; ideal for retail or exhibition pods where audiences see multiple sides.
- **Stretch Fabric:** elasticated edges hug cocktail tables or tall displays; works well outdoors in breezy conditions.

- **Sizing:** standard 4 ft, 6 ft, and 8 ft trestle dimensions plus custom measurements for reception desks or counters.

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths
chunks.chunk:
## Branding Methods
- **Full-Colour Dye Sublimation:** best for all-over coverage, gradients, patterns, and photography; artwork saturates the fabric for long-lasting colour.
- **Heat-Applied Vinyl Panels:** cost-effective for spot logos on stock-colour cloths; suitable for single or dual colour designs.

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths
chunks.chunk:
## Care Instructions
- Machine wash on cool setting with mild detergent; avoid bleach or fabric softener.
- Air-dry or tumble-dry low; remove promptly to minimise creasing.
- Store folded in supplied bags; steam or lightly iron (poly-safe setting) before events if required.

chunks.title: Custom Branded Tablecloths
chunks.chunk:
## Support
- Contact the team for sizing help, design templates, Pantone matching, or rush-order availability.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Overview
- Turn work vehicles into rolling advertisements with custom decals, partial wraps, or full livery.
- In-house design team leverages scaled vehicle drawings or on-site measurements to visualise concepts.
- Professional installers apply graphics at the Kidderminster unit, on late-evening/weekend slots, or at customer sites (subject to access and weather).

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering Workflow
1. **Consultation** – book a free visit or drop-in to capture measurements/photos. Standard vehicles use a drawing library; off-spec models get hands-on assessment.
2. **Design & Quote** – send logos/briefs for mockups; in-house team can develop new branding if required. Receive pricing with visual proofs.
3. **Approval** – confirm artwork and schedule production/installation (late-night Wednesday or Saturday slots available; mobile installs offered).
4. **Installation** – bring the vehicle in or host the team on-site. Fully insured installers handle prep and fitting; DIY supply (rolled or pre-cut graphics) available on request.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Pricing Guidelines (typical ranges)
- **Cars & “Caddy” Vans:** £200–£400 for all sides plus optional bonnet logo.
- **SWB–LWB “Transit” Vans:** £300–£550 for full panel coverage.
- **Luton / Box Vans:** £500–£800 for full sides plus optional bonnet.
- Pricing reflects cut vinyl and/or digitally printed vinyl applied to each panel; final costs depend on design complexity, coverage, and vinyl choice.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Why It Pays Off
- A one-time investment (~£500) delivers constant advertising 24/7, reaching thousands of drivers annually.
- Graphics elevate professionalism on-site and differentiate services from competitors.
- For temporary branding needs, see the companion article on magnetic vehicle signs.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Vinyl Options

### Printed Vinyl
- Best for multi-colour artwork, gradients, photos, textures, metallic, fluorescent, glitter, or holographic effects.
- Printed onto white/clear vinyl then laminated (matt or gloss) for UV and abrasion resistance.
- Easier “peel-and-stick” application but thicker material can be harder to remove years later.

### Cut Vinyl
- Precision-cut from pre-coloured polymeric films; no background so surface colour shows through.
- Ideal for simple logos, lettering, and solid shapes; metallic/neon/glitter films available.
- Layers of multiple colours can be combined for more complex designs.
- Thin profile gives a painted look and is easier to remove without tearing.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Vinyl Specifications
- **Gloss Polymeric:** 36 colour palette, permanent acrylic adhesive, 5–7 year exterior life (10+ year films available).
- **Matt Polymeric:** 37 colours, permanent adhesive, 3–5 year exterior life (longer for black/white). Resistant to UV, seawater, oils, hydrocarbons; self-extinguishing.
- Both formats conform well to curves and are suited for long-term exterior use.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Application Considerations
- Printed vinyl closely mimics traditional stickers; cut vinyl requires more precise installation and layering.
- Colour Matching: printed vinyl matches Pantone/RGB/CMYK references; cut vinyl limited to stock colours (complex logos may need simplification).
- Finishes: printed vinyl relies on laminate choice; cut vinyl offers metallic, neon, brushed, chrome, glitter, etc.
- Longevity: cut vinyl resists fade longer because colour runs through the material; printed vinyl relies on laminate for UV protection.
- Removal: printed vinyl is thicker and can snap when peeling; cut vinyl is thinner but requires patience to lift edges.

chunks.title: Vehicle Signwriting & Fleet Graphics
chunks.chunk:
## Installation & Support
- Professional team travels across the Midlands with full insurance, access equipment, and flexible scheduling; removal services available.
- DIY kits supplied with application tape, positioning guides, and care instructions for confident self-fit.

chunks.title: Window Privacy Film
chunks.chunk:
## Overview
- Etched vinyl delivers a sandblasted, translucent finish that obscures interiors while allowing natural light.
- Ideal for homes (net curtain alternative), bathrooms, kitchens, and office partitions or meeting rooms.
- Can double as glass manifestation to meet safety regulations when applied at required heights.

chunks.title: Window Privacy Film
chunks.chunk:
## Ordering Workflow
1. **Site Survey or Self-Measure** – team can visit to capture measurements/photos, or you can submit your own.
2. **Design + Quote** – designers prepare visuals showing coverage, cut-outs, or patterns; logo design available if needed.
3. **Approval** – confirm artwork and schedule production/installation.
4. **Installation** – insured installers apply film on-site; DIY supply (roll or cut-to-size with decals) available.

chunks.title: Window Privacy Film
chunks.chunk:
## Customisation Options
- **Full Coverage:** maximizes privacy; various translucency levels demonstrate how shapes appear in different lighting.
- **Cut-Outs:** add branding, text, or directional icons.
- **Layered Decals:** combine coloured vinyl behind etched film for illuminated, lightbox-style effects at night.
- **Patterns & Colours:** choose from stock motifs or custom artwork; lighter/heavier opacities and coloured frosts offered.

chunks.title: Window Privacy Film
chunks.chunk:
## Installation Support
- Professional team covers Midlands homes and workplaces with bubble-free application and access equipment as required.
- DIY kits include pre-cut panels, fixings, and guidance for confident self-installation.

chunks.title: Window Privacy Film
chunks.chunk:
## Care Instructions
- Wait 3 weeks after fitting before first clean.
- Clean with mild soapy water using a soft cloth or paper towel; avoid abrasive cleaners.
- For printed films or intricate cut-outs, wipe gently around exposed edges; do not use squeegees or excessive pressure.
